  "body": "We should avoid usage of synchronous version of `eth.sendTransaction` inside the jail in order to make calls to the jail non-blocking.\r\n\r\nFor `/send` command this means that:\r\n1. Command will be send immediately, even if transaction hasn’t been completed yet\r\n2. Command’s message object will contain transaction’s status (like `:not-completed`, `discarded`, `sent`, `confirmed`, maybe just first two for now) \r\n3. On `eth.sendTransaction` callback we will send signal from the jail which will update transaction’s status in command’s message\r\n4. We will need to rerun preview for message\r\n5. We will sent this update to all participant in the chat, preview should be affected on their side as well\r\n\r\nCurrently handler looks like\r\n```js\r\nfunction handleSend(params, context) {\r\n    var val = ...;\r\n\r\n    var data = {\r\n        ...\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n        return web3.eth.sendTransaction(data);\r\n    } catch (err) {\r\n        return {error: err.message};\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nit will be changed to something like\r\n```js\r\nfunction handleSend(params, context) {\r\n    var val = ...;\r\n\r\n    var data = {\r\n        ...\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    var messageId = status.getCurrentMessageId();\r\n    web3.eth.sendTransaction(data, function (error, hash) {\r\n        if(error) {\r\n            status.updateMessageData(messageId, {\r\n                status: \"failed\"\r\n            })\r\n        } else {\r\n            status.updateMessageData(messageId, {\r\n                status: \"sent\",\r\n                hash: hash\r\n            })\r\n        }\r\n    });\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        messageData: {\r\n            status: `not-confirmed`\r\n        }\r\n    };\r\n}\r\n```",
